<section id="about" class="py-16 border-t border-slate-100">
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12 items-start">
    <div class="md:col-span-2 space-y-5">
      <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-slate-100 text-slate-500 text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase">
        About me
      </span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-black tracking-tighter text-slate-900">
        Career changer who actually ships.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          After several years managing logistics and procurement at Arval CZ (BNP Paribas Group),
          I made a deliberate switch into software development in 2022 — starting with an intensive
          full-stack bootcamp and landing my first dev role within months.
        </p>
        <p>
          That background in operations and project management shapes how I approach backend work:
          I think in workflows, edge cases, and real-world data — not just elegant abstractions.
          Today I'm the primary backend owner at ProCorp Solution, responsible for e-commerce,
          logistics, and admin systems across multiple client projects.
        </p>
        <p>
          I'm drawn to projects where clean API design and reliable infrastructure actually matter.
          Currently exploring AI integrations with Langchain and LLMs as a natural extension of
          backend work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

